            <title>[PIG-642] Limit after FRJ causes problems</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-642</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Script:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = load &apos;/user/pig/tests/data/singlefile/studenttab10k&apos; as (name, age,gpa);&lt;br/&gt;
b = load &apos;/user/pig/tests/data/singlefile/studenttab10k&apos; as (name, age,gpa);&lt;br/&gt;
c = join a by name, b by name using &quot;replicated&quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
d = limit c 10;&lt;br/&gt;
dump d;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Error: ERROR 2013: Moving LOLimit in front of LOFRJoin is not implemented&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is fine not to move limit and apply it after the join.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
